2285 
2286 "Shipmates, God has laid but one hand upon you; both his hands press
2287 upon me.  I have read ye by what murky light may be mine the lesson
2288 that Jonah teaches to all sinners; and therefore to ye, and still
2289 more to me, for I am a greater sinner than ye.  And now how gladly
2290 would I come down from this mast-head and sit on the hatches there
2291 where you sit, and listen as you listen, while some one of you reads
2292 ME that other and more awful lesson which Jonah teaches to ME, as a
2293 pilot of the living God.  How being an anointed pilot-prophet, or
2294 speaker of true things, and bidden by the Lord to sound those
2295 unwelcome truths in the ears of a wicked Nineveh, Jonah, appalled at
2296 the hostility he should raise, fled from his mission, and sought to
2297 escape his duty and his God by taking ship at Joppa.  But God is
2298 everywhere; Tarshish he never reached.  As we have seen, God came
2299 upon him in the whale, and swallowed him down to living gulfs of
