4864 It is well known that at the coronation of kings and queens, even
4865 modern ones, a certain curious process of seasoning them for their
4866 functions is gone through.  There is a saltcellar of state, so
4867 called, and there may be a castor of state.  How they use the salt,
4868 precisely--who knows?  Certain I am, however, that a king's head is
4869 solemnly oiled at his coronation, even as a head of salad.  Can it
4870 be, though, that they anoint it with a view of making its interior
