5554 Cetology.
5555 
5556 
5557 Already we are boldly launched upon the deep; but soon we shall be
5558 lost in its unshored, harbourless immensities.  Ere that come to pass;
5559 ere the Pequod's weedy hull rolls side by side with the barnacled
5560 hulls of the leviathan; at the outset it is but well to attend to a
5561 matter almost indispensable to a thorough appreciative understanding
5562 of the more special leviathanic revelations and allusions of all
5563 sorts which are to follow.
5564 
5565 It is some systematized exhibition of the whale in his broad genera,
5566 that I would now fain put before you.  Yet is it no easy task.  The
5567 classification of the constituents of a chaos, nothing less is here
5568 essayed.  Listen to what the best and latest authorities have laid
5569 down.
5570 
5571 "No branch of Zoology is so much involved as that which is entitled
5572 Cetology," says Captain Scoresby, A.D. 1820.
5573 
5574 "It is not my intention, were it in my power, to enter into the
5575 inquiry as to the true method of dividing the cetacea into groups and
5576 families....  Utter confusion exists among the historians of this
5577 animal" (sperm whale), says Surgeon Beale, A.D. 1839.
5578 
5579 "Unfitness to pursue our research in the unfathomable waters."
5580 "Impenetrable veil covering our knowledge of the cetacea."  "A field
5581 strewn with thorns."  "All these incomplete indications but serve to
5582 torture us naturalists."
