5672 Be it known that, waiving all argument, I take the good old fashioned
5673 ground that the whale is a fish, and call upon holy Jonah to back me.
5674 This fundamental thing settled, the next point is, in what internal
5675 respect does the whale differ from other fish.  Above, Linnaeus has
5676 given you those items.  But in brief, they are these: lungs and warm
5677 blood; whereas, all other fish are lungless and cold blooded.
5678 
5679 Next: how shall we define the whale, by his obvious externals, so as
5680 conspicuously to label him for all time to come?  To be short, then,
5681 a whale is A SPOUTING FISH WITH A HORIZONTAL TAIL.  There you have
5682 him.  However contracted, that definition is the result of expanded
5683 meditation.  A walrus spouts much like a whale, but the walrus is not
5684 a fish, because he is amphibious.  But the last term of the
5685 definition is still more cogent, as coupled with the first.  Almost
5686 any one must have noticed that all the fish familiar to landsmen have
5687 not a flat, but a vertical, or up-and-down tail.  Whereas, among
5688 spouting fish the tail, though it may be similarly shaped, invariably
5689 assumes a horizontal position.
