7500 Nor, credulous as such minds must have been, was this conceit
7501 altogether without some faint show of superstitious probability.  For
7502 as the secrets of the currents in the seas have never yet been
7503 divulged, even to the most erudite research; so the hidden ways of
7504 the Sperm Whale when beneath the surface remain, in great part,
7505 unaccountable to his pursuers; and from time to time have originated
7506 the most curious and contradictory speculations regarding them,
7507 especially concerning the mystic modes whereby, after sounding to a
7508 great depth, he transports himself with such vast swiftness to the
7509 most widely distant points.
