7511 It is a thing well known to both American and English whale-ships,
7512 and as well a thing placed upon authoritative record years ago by
7513 Scoresby, that some whales have been captured far north in the
7514 Pacific, in whose bodies have been found the barbs of harpoons darted
7515 in the Greenland seas.  Nor is it to be gainsaid, that in some of
7516 these instances it has been declared that the interval of time
7517 between the two assaults could not have exceeded very many days.
7518 Hence, by inference, it has been believed by some whalemen, that the
7519 Nor' West Passage, so long a problem to man, was never a problem to
