8666 In the sixth Christian century lived Procopius, a Christian
8667 magistrate of Constantinople, in the days when Justinian was Emperor
8668 and Belisarius general.  As many know, he wrote the history of his
8669 own times, a work every way of uncommon value.  By the best
8670 authorities, he has always been considered a most trustworthy and
8671 unexaggerating historian, except in some one or two particulars, not
8672 at all affecting the matter presently to be mentioned.
