8696 In the Propontis, as far as I can learn, none of that peculiar
8697 substance called BRIT is to be found, the aliment of the right whale.
8698 But I have every reason to believe that the food of the sperm
8699 whale--squid or cuttle-fish--lurks at the bottom of that sea, because
8700 large creatures, but by no means the largest of that sort, have been
8701 found at its surface.  If, then, you properly put these statements
8702 together, and reason upon them a bit, you will clearly perceive that,
8703 according to all human reasoning, Procopius's sea-monster, that for
8704 half a century stove the ships of a Roman Emperor, must in all
8705 probability have been a sperm whale.
