9461 danger; considering that the pursuit of whales is always under great
9462 and extraordinary difficulties; that every individual moment, indeed,
9463 then comprises a peril; under these circumstances is it wise for any
9464 maimed man to enter a whale-boat in the hunt?  As a general thing,
9465 the joint-owners of the Pequod must have plainly thought not.
