9553 seen far in advance of the white bubbles at the bow.  Lit up by the
9554 moon, it looked celestial; seemed some plumed and glittering god
9555 uprising from the sea.  Fedallah first descried this jet.  For of
9556 these moonlight nights, it was his wont to mount to the main-mast
9557 head, and stand a look-out there, with the same precision as if it
9558 had been day.  And yet, though herds of whales were seen by night,
9559 not one whaleman in a hundred would venture a lowering for them.  You
9560 may think with what emotions, then, the seamen beheld this old
