9841 to heart; probably, because he knows that he has a few foibles
9842 himself.
9843 
9844 So, then, we see that of all ships separately sailing the sea, the
9845 whalers have most reason to be sociable--and they are so.  Whereas,
9846 some merchant ships crossing each other's wake in the mid-Atlantic,
9847 will oftentimes pass on without so much as a single word of
9848 recognition, mutually cutting each other on the high seas, like a
