12375 was concluded; and when, accordingly, Queequeg and a forecastle
12376 seaman came on deck, no small excitement was created among the
12377 sharks; for immediately suspending the cutting stages over the side,
12378 and lowering three lanterns, so that they cast long gleams of light
12379 over the turbid sea, these two mariners, darting their long
12380 whaling-spades, kept up an incessant murdering of the sharks,* by
12381 striking the keen steel deep into their skulls, seemingly their only
12382 vital part.  But in the foamy confusion of their mixed and struggling
12383 hosts, the marksmen could not always hit their mark; and this brought
12384 about new revelations of the incredible ferocity of the foe.  They
12385 viciously snapped, not only at each other's disembowelments, but like
12386 flexible bows, bent round, and bit their own; till those entrails
