14411 broken circles in the air, vainly striving to escape the piratical
14412 hawks.  But the bird has a voice, and with plaintive cries will make
14413 known her fear; but the fear of this vast dumb brute of the sea, was
14414 chained up and enchanted in him; he had no voice, save that choking
14415 respiration through his spiracle, and this made the sight of him
14416 unspeakably pitiable; while still, in his amazing bulk, portcullis
