16218 There are two royal fish so styled by the English law writers--the
16219 whale and the sturgeon; both royal property under certain
16220 limitations, and nominally supplying the tenth branch of the crown's
16221 ordinary revenue.  I know not that any other author has hinted of the
16222 matter; but by inference it seems to me that the sturgeon must be
16223 divided in the same way as the whale, the King receiving the highly
16224 dense and elastic head peculiar to that fish, which, symbolically
16225 regarded, may possibly be humorously grounded upon some presumed
16226 congeniality.  And thus there seems a reason in all things, even in
16227 law.
