16575 I opine, that it is plainly traceable to the first arrival of the
16576 Greenland whaling ships in London, more than two centuries ago.
16577 Because those whalemen did not then, and do not now, try out their
16578 oil at sea as the Southern ships have always done; but cutting up the
16579 fresh blubber in small bits, thrust it through the bung holes of
16580 large casks, and carry it home in that manner; the shortness of the
