16786 A Squeeze of the Hand.
16787 
16788 
16789 That whale of Stubb's, so dearly purchased, was duly brought to the
16790 Pequod's side, where all those cutting and hoisting operations
16791 previously detailed, were regularly gone through, even to the baling
16792 of the Heidelburgh Tun, or Case.
16793 
16794 While some were occupied with this latter duty, others were employed
16795 in dragging away the larger tubs, so soon as filled with the sperm;
16796 and when the proper time arrived, this same sperm was carefully
16797 manipulated ere going to the try-works, of which anon.
16798 
16799 It had cooled and crystallized to such a degree, that when, with
16800 several others, I sat down before a large Constantine's bath of it, I
16801 found it strangely concreted into lumps, here and there rolling about
16802 in the liquid part.  It was our business to squeeze these lumps back
16803 into fluid.  A sweet and unctuous duty!  No wonder that in old times
16804 this sperm was such a favourite cosmetic.  Such a clearer! such a
16805 sweetener! such a softener! such a delicious molifier!  After
16806 having my hands in it for only a few minutes, my fingers felt like
16807 eels, and began, as it were, to serpentine and spiralise.
16808 
16809 As I sat there at my ease, cross-legged on the deck; after the bitter
16810 exertion at the windlass; under a blue tranquil sky; the ship under
16811 indolent sail, and gliding so serenely along; as I bathed my hands
16812 among those soft, gentle globules of infiltrated tissues, woven
16813 almost within the hour; as they richly broke to my fingers, and
16814 discharged all their opulence, like fully ripe grapes their wine; as
16815 I snuffed up that uncontaminated aroma,--literally and truly, like
16816 the smell of spring violets; I declare to you, that for the time I
16817 lived as in a musky meadow; I forgot all about our horrible oath; in
16818 that inexpressible sperm, I washed my hands and my heart of it; I
16819 almost began to credit the old Paracelsan superstition that sperm is
16820 of rare virtue in allaying the heat of anger; while bathing in that
16821 bath, I felt divinely free from all ill-will, or petulance, or
16822 malice, of any sort whatsoever.
16823 
16824 Squeeze! squeeze! squeeze! all the morning long; I squeezed that
16825 sperm till I myself almost melted into it; I squeezed that sperm till
16826 a strange sort of insanity came over me; and I found myself
16827 unwittingly squeezing my co-laborers' hands in it, mistaking their
16828 hands for the gentle globules.  Such an abounding, affectionate,
16829 friendly, loving feeling did this avocation beget; that at last I was
16830 continually squeezing their hands, and looking up into their eyes
16831 sentimentally; as much as to say,--Oh! my dear fellow beings, why
16832 should we longer cherish any social acerbities, or know the slightest
16833 ill-humor or envy!  Come; let us squeeze hands all round; nay, let us
16834 all squeeze ourselves into each other; let us squeeze ourselves
16835 universally into the very milk and sperm of kindness.
