16851 First comes white-horse, so called, which is obtained from the
16852 tapering part of the fish, and also from the thicker portions of his
16853 flukes.  It is tough with congealed tendons--a wad of muscle--but
16854 still contains some oil.  After being severed from the whale, the
16855 white-horse is first cut into portable oblongs ere going to the
16856 mincer.  They look much like blocks of Berkshire marble.
