16858 Plum-pudding is the term bestowed upon certain fragmentary parts of
16859 the whale's flesh, here and there adhering to the blanket of blubber,
16860 and often participating to a considerable degree in its unctuousness.
16861 It is a most refreshing, convivial, beautiful object to behold.  As
16862 its name imports, it is of an exceedingly rich, mottled tint, with a
16863 bestreaked snowy and golden ground, dotted with spots of the deepest
16864 crimson and purple.  It is plums of rubies, in pictures of citron.
16865 Spite of reason, it is hard to keep yourself from eating it.  I
16866 confess, that once I stole behind the foremast to try it.  It tasted
16867 something as I should conceive a royal cutlet from the thigh of Louis
16868 le Gros might have tasted, supposing him to have been killed the
16869 first day after the venison season, and that particular venison
16870 season contemporary with an unusually fine vintage of the vineyards
16871 of Champagne.
