16929 wondrous cistern in the whale's huge head; not the prodigy of his
16930 unhinged lower jaw; not the miracle of his symmetrical tail; none of
16931 these would so surprise you, as half a glimpse of that unaccountable
16932 cone,--longer than a Kentuckian is tall, nigh a foot in diameter at
16933 the base, and jet-black as Yojo, the ebony idol of Queequeg.  And an
16934 idol, indeed, it is; or, rather, in old times, its likeness was.
16935 Such an idol as that found in the secret groves of Queen Maachah in
16936 Judea; and for worshipping which, King Asa, her son, did depose her,
16937 and destroyed the idol, and burnt it for an abomination at the brook
16938 Kedron, as darkly set forth in the 15th chapter of the First Book of
16939 Kings.
