16942 assisted by two allies, heavily backs the grandissimus, as the
16943 mariners call it, and with bowed shoulders, staggers off with it as
16944 if he were a grenadier carrying a dead comrade from the field.
16945 Extending it upon the forecastle deck, he now proceeds cylindrically
16946 to remove its dark pelt, as an African hunter the pelt of a boa.
