19263 
19264 During all this, Queequeg lay with closed eyes, as if in a dream.
19265 Pip was led away, and the sick man was replaced in his hammock.
19266 
19267 But now that he had apparently made every preparation for death; now
19268 that his coffin was proved a good fit, Queequeg suddenly rallied;
19269 soon there seemed no need of the carpenter's box: and thereupon,
