19285 length after sitting on the windlass for a few indolent days (but
19286 eating with a vigorous appetite) he suddenly leaped to his feet,
19287 threw out his arms and legs, gave himself a good stretching, yawned
19288 a little bit, and then springing into the head of his hoisted boat,
19289 and poising a harpoon, pronounced himself fit for a fight.
