22829 keel; but turning under water, swiftly shot to the surface again, far
22830 off the other bow, but within a few yards of Ahab's boat, where, for
22831 a time, he lay quiescent.
22832 
22833 "I turn my body from the sun.  What ho, Tashtego! let me hear thy
22834 hammer.  Oh! ye three unsurrendered spires of mine; thou uncracked
22835 keel; and only god-bullied hull; thou firm deck, and haughty helm,
22836 and Pole-pointed prow,--death-glorious ship! must ye then perish,
22837 and without me?  Am I cut off from the last fond pride of meanest
22838 shipwrecked captains?  Oh, lonely death on lonely life!  Oh, now I
22839 feel my topmost greatness lies in my topmost grief.  Ho, ho! from all
22840 your furthest bounds, pour ye now in, ye bold billows of my whole
22841 foregone life, and top this one piled comber of my death!  Towards
22842 thee I roll, thou all-destroying but unconquering whale; to the last
22843 I grapple with thee; from hell's heart I stab at thee; for hate's
22844 sake I spit my last breath at thee.  Sink all coffins and all hearses
22845 to one common pool! and since neither can be mine, let me then tow to
22846 pieces, while still chasing thee, though tied to thee, thou damned
22847 whale!  THUS, I give up the spear!"
22848 
22849 The harpoon was darted; the stricken whale flew forward; with
22850 igniting velocity the line ran through the grooves;--ran foul.  Ahab
22851 stooped to clear it; he did clear it; but the flying turn caught him
22852 round the neck, and voicelessly as Turkish mutes bowstring their
22853 victim, he was shot out of the boat, ere the crew knew he was gone.
22854 Next instant, the heavy eye-splice in the rope's final end flew out
22855 of the stark-empty tub, knocked down an oarsman, and smiting the sea,
22856 disappeared in its depths.
22857 
22858 For an instant, the tranced boat's crew stood still; then turned.
22859 "The ship?  Great God, where is the ship?"  Soon they through dim,
22860 bewildering mediums saw her sidelong fading phantom, as in the
22861 gaseous Fata Morgana; only the uppermost masts out of water; while
22862 fixed by infatuation, or fidelity, or fate, to their once lofty
22863 perches, the pagan harpooneers still maintained their sinking
22864 lookouts on the sea.  And now, concentric circles seized the lone
22865 boat itself, and all its crew, and each floating oar, and every
22866 lance-pole, and spinning, animate and inanimate, all round and round
22867 in one vortex, carried the smallest chip of the Pequod out of sight.
22868 
22869 But as the last whelmings intermixingly poured themselves over the
22870 sunken head of the Indian at the mainmast, leaving a few inches of
22871 the erect spar yet visible, together with long streaming yards of the
22872 flag, which calmly undulated, with ironical coincidings, over the
22873 destroying billows they almost touched;--at that instant, a red arm
22874 and a hammer hovered backwardly uplifted in the open air, in the act
22875 of nailing the flag faster and yet faster to the subsiding spar.  A
22876 sky-hawk that tauntingly had followed the main-truck downwards from
22877 its natural home among the stars, pecking at the flag, and
22878 incommoding Tashtego there; this bird now chanced to intercept its
22879 broad fluttering wing between the hammer and the wood; and
22880 simultaneously feeling that etherial thrill, the submerged savage
22881 beneath, in his death-gasp, kept his hammer frozen there; and so the
22882 bird of heaven, with archangelic shrieks, and his imperial beak
22883 thrust upwards, and his whole captive form folded in the flag of
22884 Ahab, went down with his ship, which, like Satan, would not sink to
22885 hell till she had dragged a living part of heaven along with her, and
22886 helmeted herself with it.
22887 
22888 Now small fowls flew screaming over the yet yawning gulf; a sullen
22889 white surf beat against its steep sides; then all collapsed, and the
22890 great shroud of the sea rolled on as it rolled five thousand years
22891 ago.
