22896 
22897 "AND I ONLY AM ESCAPED ALONE TO TELL THEE"
22898 Job.
22899 
22900 The drama's done.  Why then here does any one step forth?--Because
22901 one did survive the wreck.
22902 
22903 It so chanced, that after the Parsee's disappearance, I was he whom
22904 the Fates ordained to take the place of Ahab's bowsman, when that
22905 bowsman assumed the vacant post; the same, who, when on the last day
22906 the three men were tossed from out of the rocking boat, was dropped
22907 astern.  So, floating on the margin of the ensuing scene, and in full
22908 sight of it, when the halfspent suction of the sunk ship reached me,
22909 I was then, but slowly, drawn towards the closing vortex.  When I
22910 reached it, it had subsided to a creamy pool.  Round and round, then,
22911 and ever contracting towards the button-like black bubble at the axis
22912 of that slowly wheeling circle, like another Ixion I did revolve.
22913 Till, gaining that vital centre, the black bubble upward burst; and
22914 now, liberated by reason of its cunning spring, and, owing to its
22915 great buoyancy, rising with great force, the coffin life-buoy shot
22916 lengthwise from the sea, fell over, and floated by my side.  Buoyed
22917 up by that coffin, for almost one whole day and night, I floated on a
22918 soft and dirgelike main.  The unharming sharks, they glided by as if
22919 with padlocks on their mouths; the savage sea-hawks sailed with
22920 sheathed beaks.  On the second day, a sail drew near, nearer, and
22921 picked me up at last.  It was the devious-cruising Rachel, that in
22922 her retracing search after her missing children, only found another
22923 orphan.
